content: My baby came at 34 weeks so I was unable to really use most parts of this app when my delivery had to be in a hospital instead of with my midwives at my birth center. The content is great, but the app functions need to be more optimized.
Wonderfully calming and helpful. Used throughout third trimester and while in the hospital. Helped me focus and remember that God is in control.

Brilliant CHRIST-centred app! Helps reduce fear and focus on GOD'S perfect plan for you and your baby. With audio scriptures, prayers, birth affirmation cards, blogs, videos, Facebook group, hospital list etc for pregnancy, labour, birth and beyond! (I'm 31 weeks pregnant with my second child, and highly recommend this)!
I love this app. I used it in 2019 for baby number 5 and it worked for me. Now I am using it again for baby number 6. I definitely recommend!!
Love this app. I listen to it before bed. It relaxes me and helps me sleep! I pray it will have very similar effects during labor! Very calming voice.
Wonderful, helpful app. Would recommend it! Love it

I joined an online hypnobirthing course at 20 weeks, but really wanted more than just believing in myself.. as I know I can only ever do anything through God. I found this app and truly it has made all the difference. I am not scared of what is to come and love all the scriptures the strength prayer... looking forward to welcoming my baby girl into this world with the help of the Album.
Love the positive information on this app, I especially benefit from the meditation clips.
I am currently in my third trimester and love this app. It has helped me get into a much calmer state of mind as my due date approaches.

Loving this app so far! It is helping me get in a good mental space before my birth, reminds me of biblical truth and affirmations, and helps me relax. Looking forward to using it during my birth. Thank you for such a great resource!
I am thankful for this app and the positive ways it's helping me prepare for birth. Even without labor and birth in mind, the Scripture meditation is very wondeful!
I really like the scripture and positive birth affirmations. I started using it at 33 weeks to help prepare me mentally, emotionally, and spiritually for labor. Thank you!

This app was a game changer for me. I used traditional hypnobirthing prior to hearing about it, but was missing the Christian aspect. A friend in a Mommy group recommended it to me and I used it during my labor with baby #6. It was such a beautiful experience and I tell every expecting Mama I know about it!

The app is very easy to use and read. I felt very safe using the messages in the app - it was very sound - nothing that felt off or alarming to me, and I'm very very conservative with what I expose my mind to. Always use discernment with any philosophy you are learning about - but for me - so far so good.
Never have come across such an amazing app, tracks and info has helped me throughout my pregnancy journey, highly recommend!

So happy to have found this! I have taken a hypnobirthing class before and there was so much in the class that contradicts my faith as a Catholic. I just downloaded this app today and am looking forward to working through the scripts.
This is a beautiful app. It is a wonderful tool for birth preperation.
Very little material to listen, disappointed
replyContent: Hi Monika, sorry you’re disappointed. Our app has almost an hour of breathing exercises, affirmations, encouraging scriptures and more, for just over $5... so I’m not really sure what you were expecting? We appreciate your feedback though and will work to add more tracks in the coming year. God bless and Happy Christmas!

content: Really loving this app, helping me stay positive during my pregnancy and leaving my pregnancy in Gods hands.
replyContent: Thank you so much for this beautiful review Charlotte! We pray you have an amazing pregnancy and birth. God bless!

content: I enjoy this app so much. I am using it along side the Gentle Birth App to prepare for my up coming birth. This is already helping me rest better and learn to get my mind and body into a deep state of relaxation. I'll let you know after the birth how it was during actually birthing but I know it surely will not hurt and bringing God into the center focus of anything is always good!
replyContent: Thank you for your review! So glad to hear you’re enjoying the app Jeana! We pray you have a beautiful birth experience. God bless you and your family.

content: I Love This app! It has helped bring me closer to God in so many ways and has helped with all my anxiety and fears. I love listening to the encouraging scripture! I would definitely recommend to anyone!!
replyContent: Thanks for this wonderful review Laura! We appreciate it so much. We pray you have an amazing birth. God bless!

content: I really enjoyed using this app for my first pregnancy and now for my second! I love the scriptures incorporated into it. Definitely gets you in a positive, empowering mindset, which helped me mentally prepare for my births. Would recommend!
replyContent: Thank you so much for this beautiful review! So grateful we were able to be a part of your first birth journey, and now your second as well! We pray you have a wonderful birth! If you’re interested in sharing your birth story with us on our blog please get in touch (info@christianhypnobirthing.com). God bless!

content: This app has helped me tremendously with focusing on God and the natural process of birth. It is helping me to breathe through my contractions and rely on God for my strength. So grateful I found something like this for when labor is at its peak! 🙏🏽💖

Wonderful app- highly recommend!!! I'm 30 weeks pregnant, and I have been using the guided meditations to help prepare for the birth of not only my heart's wishes but an opportunity to connect deeply with Him! Thank you for making these amazing resources affordable and accessible! UPDATE: I had the unmedicated birth of my dreams thanks to God, prayers, support, and this app! I listened in the car on way to hospital, and it helped both me and hubby immensely!!
Really love this app! It is simple and the audio tracks are fantastic!
Easy to use. I listen to the tracks everyday. Hope there can be more tracks uploaded!

Listened to these tracks basically every single night! Best birthing experiencing ever and now my little boy calms to the sound of the relaxation track. Amazing! I still listen to these tracks if I'm struggling to sleep or need something positive to boost my energy for the day.
Only been using this for one day but have found it so much better than just straight hypnobirthing apps. Love that the relaxations have a scripture focus.
It's helped me relax during my pregnancy.
Great app, loved listening to the scripture and positive affirmations to prepare for my birth

soo helpful in calming my nerves & fear surrounding childbirth. i love being reminded that the Lord is for me & my baby, He is in control, & created my body to birth. thank you for such a wonderful resource! many blessings 🙏💙
I listened to the bible verses in the weeks leading to my labour. It brought calmness and positivity to me especially in times when I was stressed due to the pandemic.
I'm glad to have access to a Christian based hynobirthing app! I'm looking forward to using for my birth!
Such a wonderful and easy to use app! Uplifting and faith building definitely thankful a friend recommended it to me. I'll be sure to tell others about it
This app helped me so much when I was getting induced and wanted to connect with my body to focus on labor and delivery

Perfect for me! I love the focus of Jesus through each track. The tracks are so soothing and perfect for winding down before bed, especially if you struggle with comfortable sleep during your pregnancy. You will get about 90 minutes of tracks to listen to for the one-time purchase.
Best app to help me prepare for labor and childbirth with my faith at the very center! Exactly what I need!!!
I like this app. It's easy to use and helpful!
Love this app - super easy to use and great info! I also like the downloadable tracks!
replyContent: Thank you so much for the wonderful feedback! We pray you have an amazing pregnancy and birth. Blessings!

content: This is *exactly* what I was looking for. I'm enjoying listening to the tracks. They are helping me to focus without the new age self-focus aspect of typical hypnobirthing tracks. I feel like this is going to make ALL the difference with my second birth.
replyContent: Thank you so much for this wonderful feedback! So thrilled to hear that the spiritual aspect of the app means so much to you. We pray you have a blessed and wonderful birth!

content: Absolutelt love this app. I was on the fence with hypnobirthing since I feel hypnosis and the Christian faith don't mix. However, this is truly different. All the relaxation techniques without the spiritual vulnerability that can be brought on by hypnosis. All "meditation" is on scriptures and prayer and all of the "affirmations" are just scriptures/Biblical truths to help you maintain confidence in His design of the temple God has created for us as birthing women. Super cool!!
replyContent: Really thrilled to hear that you’ve been enjoying using the app! And particularly that the spiritual aspect has been so important to you. God bless!

content: Absolutely love this app Wife had listened to it nearly ever night now Thank you
replyContent: I’m so thrilled to hear that! Many blessings to you and your wife. We pray that she has a wonderful pregnancy and birth!

content: I love relaxing and focusing on our Lord. I know He will be with me throughout my birth. The tracks on this app are very soothing! Love it!
replyContent: So grateful to hear you find the track soothing! We pray you have a blessed and wonderful birth.

content: I has heard great things about this app and decided to give it a try. It's been very helpful to me in my last trimester and I look forward to using it during birth.
replyContent: It’s so great to hear that you heard good things about the app and decided to give it a try! Really grateful to hear it’s also been helpful to you! We pray you have an amazing birth.

content: I've stumbled across this app after a friend has mentioned Christian Hypnobirthing to me. I didn't realise something like this would exist. I absolutely love this app and am really excited to use it at the labour and delivery of our first in 3 weeks time! I have meditated over the scriptures myself and have written down some of the affirmations in order to process them even better. A great way of practising breathing techniques alongside solid Bible scripture. I highly recommend this app!
replyContent: Thank you for this wonderful and very thoughtful review! We pray that you have such an amazing birth and would love to hear about it if you fancy sharing. Just send us an email with your birth story to info@ChristianHypnobirthing.com Blessings!

content: I listened to the meditations, music, & scripture every night for the last two months leading up to delivery... I was reminded that God is in control & created me for all aspects of being a momma. I was also able to use the app during labor (which was amazing). I believe my heart/soul being at peace, allowed my body to progress like it needed to. I am expecting again & have already started listening to it as doubt/fear starts to creep in. I have also gifted this app to my best friend. 10/10!!
replyContent: Wow! What a beautiful review. So so thrilled to hear you found the app helpful during labour. And many congratulations on your current pregnancy as well! We pray the app can help you again throughout this next labour. And that you have a wonderful pregnancy and birth. Blessings!

content: Really helpful and encouraging. It is a real blessing to me in my pregnancy! Thank you.
replyContent: Thank you for the beautiful feedback! So thrilled to hear that. We pray you have a wonderful birth. Blessings!

content: Found these affirmations and tracks very useful in preparation for birth. We had a very calm hypnobirth ❤️
replyContent: Many congratulations! And thank you for this beautiful review. So grateful to hear you had a calm Hypnobirth. God bless!

content: Her voice and the music is soothing. I really enjoy listening to these tracks.
replyContent: Thank you for this lovely review! So thrilled that you found the app soothing. We pray you have a wonderful birth! God bless.

content: So glad I fould this app. I didnt realize such a good app exists, it was all I needed- affirmations in Christ, that bring me closer to God. I listened to the tracks daily before falling asleep at night and during my short relaxing breaks during the day. I had it on during the labor. I love that the tracks were not noo long and at the same time powerful, encouraging and inspiring. I wish I had the app for my previous births, too. Highly reccommend!

Great so far! Having a Spiritually filled birth is super important to my husband and I, and this App has hit the spot! It's relaxing, encouraging and empowering and I'm excited that I found something Christian based to help us. The app itself is very user friendly and I haven't had any crashes or problems. I 100% reccomend.
So far I am enjoying the positive affirmations and scripture!

I have only had this app for a couple of days and have been telling all my friends about it. The scriptures are straight from the Bible no altering or rephrasing which is a MUST for me! Such an amazing app cannot wait to use it during labor!

I was hesitant about this app because some reviews said that the tracks would stop, but I haven't had that experience. I did download everything into a different player, which is super easy to do, because I wanted to put together a playlist that would include these and other hypnobirthing tracks. I love these tracks though, as a Christian, being reminded and focused on God and his goodness during childbirth and having a tool that helps with that is awesome!

I love using this app! I really liked the general concept of hypnobirthing, but as a Christian some of the affirmations and some of the scripts did not resonate with my beliefs. This app has really helped to reframe hypnobirthing in a way that glorifies our great God!

Great app! Exactly what I wanted. I love the hypobirthing method but wanted something to add to my birth tool box. Something that had spiritual substance that matched my beliefs. Same breathing techniques as "secular" hypobirthing, same type music, voice, etc. But the scriptural affirmations is the cherry on top. Very encouraging. Feed your soul and confidence in the strength of God. Can't wait to play during our birth in October 2020. Also app is very user friendly and easy to navigate.

This app is great! I loved the prayer track the most and really helped me stay focused on the beautiful blessings God was providing during pregancy. I know that I have an awesome tool to use during birth!

User friendly, straight forward and good for the price. The tracks have download capabilities, so it doesn't require WiFi or Data to listen to which will be handy come time to give birth. The voice is very soothing and I Love the visualization track of the flower opening up. It has been very important to my husband and I that we have a spirit filled pregnancy and birth, so I was thrilled when I found this app!
Very soothing sounds, verses and voices. I'm looking forward to using this during labor in combination with the Calm app to help keep me calm and focused.
Love the content! So convenient! I do wish the navigation was a little more streamlined with less buffering, but we'll worth it!
The app never opened on my phone so it was useless

content: Saved me! Helped me survive when baby came too fast to get an epidural like my other deliveries. So calming and strengthening. Helped heal previous birth traumas and trust God.

content: I really loved listening to this during my birth. It really put an eternal perspective on the sacred experience of bringing a child of God into the world. There was a moment though right when I was birthing my baby that the recording was casting satan out of the room. I didn't find that necessary at all.
replyContent: Hi Sarah, thanks so much for your feedback. ‘Satan’ is only mentioned twice on the album, in the ‘Prayers for Strength’ track, which is specifically to help empower people to overcome anything that may not be coming from God (e.g. fear or pain etc), and is based on what Jesus gave us the power to do (Luke 10:19). I hope that makes sense. God bless!

content: Very disappointed :( the tracks keep stopping during each breathing exercise. How do you suppose to relax and keep in the flow of the techinic if the app does not work properly. replyContent: Hi Andrea, I am very sorry to hear that you've had issues with the app, and also that you don't own a computer and therefore can't download the app. Please contact us on info@christianhypnobirthing.com and we will organise a refund, which could go towards downloading the album onto your phone through Amazon, if you still wish to use the tracks.

content: Wonderful app. They found the most relaxing voice in the world. I even use this to fall asleep 6 months after the birth of my baby. Some things don't apply but the positive scripture, visualizations and humming background music truly puts me at peace.
replyContent: Thank you so much for this beautiful review Tammy! We're so thrilled that you have found the tracks so relaxing. Blessings to you and your family.

content: If you are pregnant, you need this for your labor and delivery! I cannot recommend this enough. I used this with my third baby, and my only regret was that I didn't know about it for my first two. I had the soundtracks playing in the room during labor and it calmed everyone in the room. My midwife, nurse, and doula all commented on how soothing it was for them as well. Christian Hypnobirthing totally redeemed my difficult first 2 births. I've never experienced anything more empowering!
replyContent: Thank you so much Jessica! We feel so grateful that the app was able to have such a wonderful impact on your labour and delivery. And so lovely of you to share your feedback. God bless!

content: Really great app and good support by email with some initial problems with the app.

content: It was a great calming relaxing app. First app I ever paid for because it was worth having an easy way to practice hypnobirthing. Made my birth peaceful and focused. I am not christian but i enjoyed it nonetheless.

content: Incredible app for preparing for birth . I listened to the encouraging scripture over and over prior to birth and I listen to it post partum as well. It is soothing and gives you a great sense of peace as your body prepares to give birth.

content: Really helped keep my mind in the right place during labor. Was able to have a natural delivery and stay calm the entire time. Was not sure I'd be able to but I think this ap really helped. Had several nurses tell me my birth was amazing and ask how I did it.

content: Very helpful in guiding my thoughts and breath patterns in preparation for birth.

content: This has been exactly what i needed. I discovered this app just a couple of weeks ago at 37 weeks pregnant and it has really been a God Send. replyContent: Thank you so much for sharing. I’m so grateful to hear that you’ve found the app so helpful. I pray the birth went brilliantly! God bless!

content: Love this app. The recordings have all the great aspects of hypnobirthing plus added scriptures and a Christian view on things.

content: This content of the app is excellent. It's so calming and soothing. Christian based with prayers and scriptures.!!!!!! Would recommend to anyone.

content: From a first time mommy's point of view, this app has helped me loads to deliver my son, I only got to download it about 2 weeks before birth but it was able to get me Into the rhytem of breathing which really helped keep me sane through the immense pain of Labour... I thank God for this app, it's excellent
replyContent: Thank you so much for this review! It’s so wonderful to hear that the app helped you feel closer to God throughout your birth, and to overcome fear by trusting Him. God bless you!

content: I only started researching hypnobirthing at 36 weeks gestation (!). The Christ-centred scriptures and affirmations were great to listen to leading up to the birth. Even the midwife asked me what I was listening to! I used other tools to help with the preparation but Thank you, this app is such a blessing!
replyContent: Thank you so much for your wonderful feedback. So grateful to hear the app helped you stay positive and focused during birth. Many blessings to you and your family!

content: Awesome in terms of scriptures, but the terminology should perhaps be changed. Surges should be used instead of contractions as for Hypnobirthing
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback! Because we’re a Christian app, there are ways where we differ from traditional Hypnobirthing. We say contractions because of Jackie Mize’s experience (in her book Supernatural Childbirth pg 36) where God showed her He has designed our muscles to contract and it doesn’t have to hurt - part of our perfect design. God bless!

content: I am a doula and this app has done absolute WONDERS for my clients. THANK YOU!
replyContent: Thank you so much for this lovely review. It means so much to us to know that the app is helping your clients! We pray it continues to do so. Thanks again for the beautiful feedback.

content: Haviing had a very stressful birth with my first child I was determined to have a better experience with my second. replyContent: It's so wonderful to hear your story and feedback - thank you so much! We pray for you to have an amazing, safe, and empowered birth. God bless you and your family!

content: I love this app. Due in Feburary and was looking through hypnobirthing courses and programs and stumbled across this. content: This app is amazing and did wonders for me during labor and delivery! I used the positive affirmations, prayers and meditation music well before labor to prep for the day. replyContent: Thank you for your review Kathryn! Sounds like such a beautiful and peaceful birth. So grateful to hear that the app was able to help you relax and trust our Heavenly Father. What a testimont to how perfectly God has designed us for birth. God bless!

content: I have not had my baby yet but it is already worth every penny- I enjoy listening to the positive affirmations, prayers, and scriptures especially. It's great for reminding us women that God designed our bodies perfectly for childbirth.

content: Already enjoying this app greatly as I prepare for another home birth.
